# Windsurf Rules — AI-First Next.js Boilerplate

You are working in a Next.js 15 App Router project. Apply these rules to every file you create or modify.

## Core Stack
Next.js 15 | React 19 | TypeScript strict | Tailwind + shadcn/ui
TanStack Query v5 | Zustand v5 | react-hook-form + Zod | ^4.0

## Architecture (strict layering)
```
app/page.tsx          (route entry)
    ↓
services/*.service.ts  (business logic)
    ↓
adapters/*.adapter.ts  (HTTP calls)
    ↓
External API
```
**RULE**: components/features/ calls services/ — NEVER adapters/ directly.

## File Placement
| Create | Put it in |
|--------|-----------|
| New page | `src/app/[route]/page.tsx` |
| New API | `src/app/api/[name]/route.ts` |
| UI primitive | `src/components/common/` |
| Business component | `src/components/features/` |
| HTTP function | `src/adapters/[domain]/[domain].adapter.ts` |
| Business logic | `src/services/[domain].service.ts` |
| Global state | `src/stores/[name].store.tsx` |
| Shared hook | `src/hooks/use-[name].ts` |
| Shared type | `src/types/[domain].types.ts` |

## Server vs Client
- Default = Server Component (no directive)
- `'use client'` only for: useState/useEffect, browser APIs, event handlers, TanStack hooks
- NEVER `'use client'` on layout.tsx

## State
- Async/API data → TanStack Query
- Shared UI state → Zustand
- Forms → react-hook-form (NEVER useState for forms)

## Naming
- Files: kebab-case | Components: PascalCase named export
- Zod | ^4.0
- Default exports ONLY for page.tsx, layout.tsx

## Never
- `fetch()` in components (use TanStack Query)
- `console.log` (use logger helper)
- Hardcoded URLs (use API_ROUTES / WEB_ROUTES)
- `any` type
- Business logic in page.tsx (use services/)
- `process.env` directly (use env from configurations/)

